  <description>Leaves: basal sometimes present (in rosettes) at flowering, proximalmost cauline
    petiolate, often present at flowering, largest, not 3-nerved. Heads in wand-shaped racemiform,
    paniculiform, or thyrsiform arrays, not secund. Phyllaries not striate, resinous (minute glands
    present). Pappus bristles usually in 2, rarely in 3 series, (shorter, outer setiform scales
    rarely present, inner bristles weakly to strongly clavate).</description>
